<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; compiler (instrumentation), and host tools (reader/writer). The entities</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; defined in this file affect the profile runtime ABI, the raw profile format,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; or both.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The file has two identical copies. The primary copy lives in LLVM and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; the other one  sits in compiler-rt/lib/profile directory. To make changes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; in this file, first modify the primary copy and copy it over to compiler-rt.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Testing of any change in this file can start only after the two copies are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; synced up.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The first part of the file includes macros that defines types, names, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; initializers for the member fields of the core data structures. The field</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; declarations for one structure is enabled by defining the field activation</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; macro associated with that structure. Only one field activation record</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; can be defined at one time and the rest definitions will be filtered out by</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Magic number to detect file format and endianness.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Use 255 at one end, since no UTF-8 file can use that character.  Avoid 0,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; so that utilities, like strings, don&#39;t grab it as a string.  129 is also</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; invalid UTF-8, and high enough to be interesting.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Use &quot;lprofr&quot; in the centre to stand for &quot;LLVM Profile Raw&quot;, or &quot;lprofR&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; for 32-bit platforms.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;RAW&#95;MAGIC&#95;64 (uint64&#95;t)255 &lt;&lt; 56 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;l&#39; &lt;&lt; 48 | \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">       (uint64&#95;t)&#39;p&#39; &lt;&lt; 40 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;r&#39; &lt;&lt; 32 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;o&#39; &lt;&lt; 24 |  \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">        (uint64&#95;t)&#39;f&#39; &lt;&lt; 16 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;r&#39; &lt;&lt; 8 | (uint64&#95;t)129</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;RAW&#95;MAGIC&#95;32 (uint64&#95;t)255 &lt;&lt; 56 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;l&#39; &lt;&lt; 48 | \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">       (uint64&#95;t)&#39;p&#39; &lt;&lt; 40 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;r&#39; &lt;&lt; 32 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;o&#39; &lt;&lt; 24 |  \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">        (uint64&#95;t)&#39;f&#39; &lt;&lt; 16 | (uint64&#95;t)&#39;R&#39; &lt;&lt; 8 | (uint64&#95;t)129</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Raw profile format version (start from 1). &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;RAW&#95;VERSION 10</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Indexed profile format version (start from 1). &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;INDEX&#95;VERSION 12</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Coverage mapping format version (start from 0). &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;COVMAP&#95;VERSION 6</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Profile version is always of type uint64&#95;t. Reserve the upper 32 bits in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; version for other variants of profile. We set the 8th most significant bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; (i.e. bit 56) to 1 to indicate if this is an IR-level instrumentation</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; generated profile, and 0 if this is a Clang FE generated profile.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; 1 in bit 57 indicates there are context-sensitive records in the profile.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 54th bit indicates whether to always instrument loop entry blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 58th bit indicates whether to always instrument function entry blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 59th bit indicates whether to use debug info to correlate profiles.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 60th bit indicates single byte coverage instrumentation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 61st bit indicates function entry instrumentation only.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 62nd bit indicates whether memory profile information is present.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The 63rd bit indicates if this is a temporal profile.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASKS&#95;ALL 0xffffffff00000000ULL</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define GET&#95;VERSION(V) ((V) &amp; ~VARIANT&#95;MASKS&#95;ALL)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;INSTR&#95;LOOP&#95;ENTRIES (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 55)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;IR&#95;PROF (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 56)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;CSIR&#95;PROF (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 57)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;INSTR&#95;ENTRY (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 58)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;DBG&#95;CORRELATE (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 59)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;BYTE&#95;COVERAGE (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 60)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;FUNCTION&#95;ENTRY&#95;ONLY (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 61)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;MEMPROF (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 62)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define VARIANT&#95;MASK&#95;TEMPORAL&#95;PROF (0x1ULL &lt;&lt; 63)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;RAW&#95;VERSION&#95;VAR &#95;&#95;llvm&#95;profile&#95;raw&#95;version</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;PROFILE&#95;RUNTIME&#95;VAR &#95;&#95;llvm&#95;profile&#95;runtime</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00989" /><CodeLine lineNumber="989"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Map an (observed) memop size value to the representative value of its range.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00990" /><CodeLine lineNumber="990"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; For example, 5 -&gt; 5, 22 -&gt; 17, 99 -&gt; 65, 256 -&gt; 256, 1001 -&gt; 513 &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00991" /><CodeLine lineNumber="991"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/profiledata/include/llvm/profiledata/coverage/coveragemapping-h/#a991a4b9fc0060d2c13c2609e8dbd5c48">INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;VISIBILITY</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprof-cpp/#a628d687cee30f0ab21adb0a276644287">INSTR&#95;PROF&#95;INLINE</a> uint64&#95;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00992" /><CodeLine lineNumber="992"><span class="doxyHighlight">InstrProfGetRangeRepValue(uint64&#95;t Value) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00993" /><CodeLine lineNumber="993"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Value &lt;= 8)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00994" /><CodeLine lineNumber="994"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The first ranges are individually tracked. Use the value as is.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00995" /><CodeLine lineNumber="995"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Value;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00996" /><CodeLine lineNumber="996"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Value &gt;= 513)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00997" /><CodeLine lineNumber="997"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The last range is mapped to its lowest value.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00998" /><CodeLine lineNumber="998"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> 513;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00999" /><CodeLine lineNumber="999"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (InstProfPopcountll(Value) == 1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01000" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1000"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If it&#39;s a power of two, use it as is.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01001" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1001"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Value;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1002"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Otherwise, take to the previous power of two + 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (UINT64&#95;C(1) &lt;&lt; (64 - InstProfClzll(Value) - 1)) + 1;</span></CodeLine>
